verses.roman:
jagadānanda dāmodara,--dui saṅge lañā
ghare āila bhaṭṭācārya jagannātha dekhiyā

synonyms: jagadānanda—of the name Jagadānanda; dāmodara—of the name Dāmodara; dui—two persons; saṅge—with him; lañā—taking; ghare—to his home; āila—returned; bhaṭṭācārya—Sārvabhauma Bhaṭṭācārya; jagannātha—Lord Jagannātha; dekhiyā—seeing in the temple.
translation: After visiting the temple of Lord Jagannātha, Sārvabhauma Bhaṭṭācārya returned home with Jagadānanda and Dāmodara.
